Some sources use the older notation,  but (1) the most often used notation today is L(z, s, a) (for example, see https://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=lerch+zeta+function), and (2) the notation is more consistent with the transcendental function on the same page as well as the notation for Hurwitz zeta function and those alike.
